  • Method Details

    • ul

      public void ul​(java.lang.String... args)
      Creates a HTML5 ul element with li elements inside. Each argument represents the content of a single li element. The li element(s) will be nested within a single unordered list (bullet point list).
      Parameters:
      args - The content of the li element(s)

    • ulID

      public void ulID​(java.lang.String id, java.lang.String... args)
      Creates a HTML5 ul element with li elements inside. Each argument represents the content of a single li element. The li element(s) will be nested within a single unordered list (bullet point list). You can give the element an ID of your choice.
      Parameters:
      id - The id you want for your HTML element
      args - The content of the li element

    • ol

      public void ol​(java.lang.String... args)
      Creates a HTML5 ol element with li elements inside. Each argument represents the content of a single li element. The li element(s) will be nested within a single ordered list (numbered list).
      Parameters:
      args - The content of the li element(s)

    • olID

      public void olID​(java.lang.String id, java.lang.String... args)
      Creates a HTML5 ol element with li elements inside. Each argument represents the content of a single li element. The li element(s) will be nested within a single ordered list (numbered list). You can give the element an ID of your choice.
      Parameters:
      id - The id you want for your HTML element
      args - The content of the li element

    • li

      public void li​(java.lang.String... args)
      Creates a HTML5 list element for every argument given. Regular HTML conventions dictate that you should not make li elements without a wrapper like ol or ul however.
      Parameters:
      args - The content of the li elements
